dcterms:description: NAS-Bench-101 is the first rigorous NAS dataset designed for benchmarking NAS methods. It targets the cell-based search space used in many popular NAS methods and contains 423,624 unique neural architectures. Each architecture comes with pre-computed validation and test accuracies on CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: NAS-Bench-101

dcterms:creator: Xuanyi Dong
Yi Yang
dcterms:description: NAS-Bench-201 employs a fixed cell-based DAG representation of neural architectures, where nodes represent the sum of feature maps and edges are associated with operations that transform the feature maps. It contains 15,625 unique neural architectures and provides training details for three datasets: CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and ImageNet-16-120.
dcterms:title: NAS-Bench-201

dcterms:creator: Hanxiao Liu
Karen Simonyan
Yiming Yang
dcterms:description: The DARTS search space is a popular search space for large-scale NAS experiments, consisting of two cells: a convolutional cell and a reduction cell, each with six nodes. It allows roughly 10^9 DAGs without considering graph isomorphism.
dcterms:title: DARTS
